    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Göttingen,</placeName>
                    <date>15. June 1879.</date>
                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>My joy at the beautiful present of</p>
                    <p rend="centre">“The Descent of Man” </p>
                    <p>and my zeal for penetrating in it are so great that I almost had forgotten there-at to thank my benevolent author;<ref target="#foot.f1"/> you will therefore kindly excuse my negligence and not take off me your high favour by which I am so inexpressibly happy.</p>
<p>With glad heart I thank you for your exceeding kindness to which I shall also show myself thankful and worthy for my all life.</p>
<p>I remain, Sir, | in all duty | your most obedient servant | Hermann Otto, stud. rer. nat.</p> 
                </div>
            </div> 
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">No other correspondence with Otto has been found. CD sent a copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref>.</note>   
        </div>
    
    </body>
